## Errors & Mistakes
- BIG DEAD END: first tried `google_adk` as a real pyproject EXTRA + uv.lock +
  conflict declarations. This CONTAMINATED the universal lock: google-adk requires
  fastapi>=0.133 / starlette>=1.0.1 (0->1 MAJOR) / google-auth>=2.47, and because
  the base resolution is shared with every extra, `uv lock` bumped the BASE
  (every shard): starlette 0.50->1.3.1, fastapi 0.122->0.137, pillow 12.0->12.2,
  rsa dropped. Proven by counterfactual: re-locking the ORIGINAL pyproject keeps
  base unchanged; only adding the extra caused it. Declaring google_adk conflicting
  with google_genai/langchain/vertexai/crewai did NOT help (base isn't an extra,
  can't be split away). Reverted the extra+conflicts+lock entirely; switched to
  the post-sync install approach (option C). LESSON: a heavy framework extra with
  high transitive floors poisons the shared universal-lock resolution; install it
  post-sync instead.
- My first (name,version) churn-diff used a grep that matched inline dep-spec
  lines, not [[package]] stanzas -- misleading. The `^name =` anchored grep
  (6 added, 0 removed) was the authoritative one.
- Initial upstream-drift test would have ERRORed on 0.62b1: importorskip doesn't
  skip (module imports fine) but GEN_AI_USAGE_REASONING_OUTPUT_TOKENS is absent
