## Hints for Future Agents
- The integration is import-hook activated (patch.py:490 maps google.adk ->
  patch_google_adk; lazy module import). It is NOT auto-triggered by
  `import google.adk` after weave.init() because the hook matches root modules
  only -- import ADK before init or call patch_google_adk() explicitly.
- google_adk shard installs google-adk POST-SYNC (noxfile, after session.run(
  *sync_args)); it is in SHARDS_WITHOUT_EXTRAS so the frozen sync stays base-only.
- The trace server vendors the SAME gen_ai.* strings (agents/semconv.py); keep
  client _semconv.py and server in lockstep or extraction silently drops attrs.
  The TestVendoredSemconv lockstep test guards this.
- ADK's wrappers must tolerate ADK adding trailing kwargs over releases; that's
  why _wrap_trace_tool_call uses **extra. The other 3 wrappers still match 2.2.0.

